x4freetext: For the excitation function measurements,
self-supporting metal foils of thulium having thickness
around 1 mg/cm**2 backed by 2 mg/cm**2 thick aluminium
catcher foils were bombarded with 12-C beam.  In each
irradiation a stack of two such target catcher
assemblies was used.

x4codes.hlp: Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Trombay, Mumbai, India

x4freetext: See sample
The duration of irradiation was about one hour
with the total charge collection of about 400 micro
Coulombs
Measured using an electron suppressed Faraday
cup placed behind the target-catcher assembly.
The time elapsed between the stoppage of beam
and the start of counting of the sample on detector
was about 5 minutes. Thus the excitation function
measurements could be carried out only for evaporation
residues having half-life more than 5 minutes.
Initially the counting time was kept as 100 seconds and
was subsequently increased to longer periods for
counting long-lived products.
-By authors.  The radioactivity produced due to
bombardment of aluminium catcher foil by the 12-C beam
is due to 146 KeV gamma-ray of 34-Cl-m which has a
half-life of 32 min.  This does not interfere with
gamma-ray energies of interest.  All other reaction
products of 12-C + 27-Al do not have suitable half
lives or gamma-rays so as to cause any interference
with the gamma-rays of interest.

x4freetext: Data tables are received from S.Chakrabarty
Subentry A0459008 is corrected.
Last checking has been done.
The errors on the cross section values are in
the range of 10-20%.  The major factors contributing to
the errors are that due to the target thickness (5%),
detection efficiency (5%) and statistical and fitting
error on the peak area (1-15%).
The uncertainty is shown on figure without
any analysis.
Complete and incomplete fusion cross sections for some
products.
- By authors. The experiment shows that the rhenium
products are formed only by deexcitation of the
compound nucleus, Re-181, in complete fusion reaction.
The fitted data obtained using PACE2 code.

than calculated data indicating the contribution from
incomplete fusion reaction.  These reactions can be of
the type 169-Tm(C-12, alpha)177-Ta(*).  The excited
177-Ta nucleus may subsequently deexcite by neutron
emission to give 175, 174, 173-Ta.
The fitted data obtained using PACE2 code.
